6c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:04.364Z"},"obs_mpyl9ykc_52f3bd2a8b53":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpyl9ykc_52f3bd2a8b53","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_1d49afe45c944814a99e1e99","duration_ms":5551,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","tool_input":"{\"libraryName\":\"Apache Seata\",\"query\":\"Seata 2.6.0 Spring Boot 3 integration Nacos configuration\"}","tool_name":"context7_resolve-library-id","tool_output":"Available Libraries:\n\n- Title: Apache Seata\n- Context7-compatible library ID: /apache/incubator-seata\n- Description: Apache Seata is a distributed transaction solution with high performance and ease of use for microservices architecture.\n- Code Snippets: 1686\n- Source Reputation: High\n- Benchmark Score: 76\n- Versions: v2.4.0"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:15.100Z","toolInput":"{\"libraryName\":\"Apache Seata\",\"query\":\"Seata 2.6.0 Spring Boot 3 integration Nacos configuration\"}","toolName":"context7_resolve-library-id","toolOutput":"Available Libraries:\n\n- Title: Apache Seata\n- Context7-compatible library ID: /apache/incubator-seata\n- Description: Apache Seata is a distributed transaction solution with high performance and ease of use for microservices architecture.\n- Code Snippets: 1686\n- Source Reputation: High\n- Benchmark Score: 76\n- Versions: v2.4.0"},"obs_mpyl9ykc_90ab55f8f064":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpyl9ykc_90ab55f8f064","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_7ee895ef77c645239f252ad2","duration_ms":5499,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","tool_input":"{\"query\":\"Apache Seata official documentation site 2026\",\"numResults\":5}","tool_name":"websearch_web_search_exa","tool_output":"Title: Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApache Seata\n[...]\n## Apache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating)\n[...]\nApache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) is an open source distributed transaction solution that delivers high performance and easy to use distributed transaction services under a microservices architecture.\n[...]\nRelease Note of v2.5.0\n[...]\nReleased on 2025/08/05\n[...]\n### What is Apache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) ?\n[...]\nSeata is an open source distributed transaction solution that delivers high performance and easy to use distributed transaction services under a microservices architecture. Before the open source of Seata, its internal version has been playing the role of middleware for data consistency of application architecture layer in Alibaba group, helping the economy to smoothly go through the Double 11 of the past year and providing strong technical support for the upper business. After years of development, its commercial products have been sold on Alibaba Cloud and Financial cloud. 2019.1 in order to create a more complete technological ecology and inclusive technological achievements, Seata officially announced open source to the outside world. In the future, Seata will organize as a community to help users quickly land distributed transaction solutions.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Introduction | Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/registry/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nIntroduction | Apache Seata\n\nVersion: v2.6\n[...]\nIntroduction | Apache Seata\n[...]\nVersion: v2.6\n\n---\n\nTitle: apache/incubator-seata\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata\nPublished: 2018-12-28T08:37:22.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n- Stars: 25970\n- Forks: 8891\n- Watchers: 25970\n- Open issues: 878\n- Primary language: Java\n- Languages: Java (97.3%), TypeScript (0.9%), ANTLR (0.8%), Shell (0.4%), Lua (0.2%), SCSS (0.2%), Kotlin, Batchfile, Python, TSQL, Dockerfile, Go Template\n- License: Apache License 2.0 (Apache-2.0)\n- Topics: at, consistency, distributed-transaction, microservice, saga, tcc, xa\n- Default branch: 2.x\n- Homepage: https://seata.apache.org/\n- Created: 2018-12-28T08:37:22Z\n- Last push: 2026-04-08T01:16:41Z\n- Contributors: 380 (top: slievrly, funky-eyes, xingfudeshi, wangliang181230, jsbxyyx, l81893521, Bughue, zjinlei, sharajava, caohdgege)\n- Releases: 45\n- Latest release: v2.6.0 (2026-01-28T15:55:30Z)\n[...]\nYou can view the full documentation from Apache Seata Official Website: Apache Seata Website page.\n[...]\n- Apache Seata Website - Apache Seata official website\n- Apache Seata GoLang - Apache Seata GoLang client\n- Apache Seata Samples - Samples for Apache Seata Java\n- Apache Seata GoLang Samples - Samples for Apache Seata GoLang\n- Apache Seata K8s - Apache Seata integration with Kubernetes\n- Apache Seata CLI - CLI tool for Apache Seata operations\n\n---\n\nTitle: Apollo Configuration Center | Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/configuration/apollo\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApollo Configuration Center | Apache Seata\n[...]\nVersion: v2.6\n[...]\n# Apollo Configuration Center\n[...]\nThe steps to integrate Seata with the Apollo Configuration Center are very simple and can be roughly divided into \"Adding Maven Dependencies\" and\n[...]\nconfiguration to Apollo-Server\".\n[...]\n### Upload Configuration to\n[...]\nConfiguration Center‚Äč\n[...]\nRefer to config.txt in https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/tree/develop/script/config-center and make modifications. Then run the provided Apollo script in the repository to submit the information to the Apollo console. If there is a need for changes, they can be directly made through the console.\n\n---\n\nTitle: apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website\nPublished: 2019-01-18T13:04:50.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApache Seata(incubating) Website\n[...]\n- Stars: 108\n- Forks: 134\n- Watchers: 108\n- Open issues: 27\n- Primary language: JavaScript\n- Languages: JavaScript (45.1%), SCSS (22.1%), TypeScript (19.4%), HTML (12.6%), CSS (0.5%), Shell (0.4%)\n- License: Apache License 2.0 (Apache-2.0)\n- Topics: article, distributed-transaction, docsite, seata-website\n- Default branch: docusaurus\n- Homepage: https://seata.apache.org/\n- Created: 2019-01-18T13:04:50Z\n- Last push: 2026-03-17T00:31:59Z\n- Contributors: 100 (top: slievrly, funky-eyes, lovepoem, liuqiufeng, zjinlei, chai001125, xingfudeshi, lightClouds917, lvekee, l81893521)\n[...]\n# Seata Official Website\n[...]\nseata website deploy on github\n[...]\nAll website material of https://seata.apache.org, which uses a open source framework: Docusaurus."},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:15.013Z","toolInput":"{\"query\":\"Apache Seata official documentation site 2026\",\"numResults\":5}","toolName":"websearch_web_search_exa","toolOutput":"Title: Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApache Seata\n[...]\n## Apache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating)\n[...]\nApache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) is an open source distributed transaction solution that delivers high performance and easy to use distributed transaction services under a microservices architecture.\n[...]\nRelease Note of v2.5.0\n[...]\nReleased on 2025/08/05\n[...]\n### What is Apache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) ?\n[...]\nSeata is an open source distributed transaction solution that delivers high performance and easy to use distributed transaction services under a microservices architecture. Before the open source of Seata, its internal version has been playing the role of middleware for data consistency of application architecture layer in Alibaba group, helping the economy to smoothly go through the Double 11 of the past year and providing strong technical support for the upper business. After years of development, its commercial products have been sold on Alibaba Cloud and Financial cloud. 2019.1 in order to create a more complete technological ecology and inclusive technological achievements, Seata officially announced open source to the outside world. In the future, Seata will organize as a community to help users quickly land distributed transaction solutions.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Introduction | Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/registry/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nIntroduction | Apache Seata\n\nVersion: v2.6\n[...]\nIntroduction | Apache Seata\n[...]\nVersion: v2.6\n\n---\n\nTitle: apache/incubator-seata\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata\nPublished: 2018-12-28T08:37:22.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n- Stars: 25970\n- Forks: 8891\n- Watchers: 25970\n- Open issues: 878\n- Primary language: Java\n- Languages: Java (97.3%), TypeScript (0.9%), ANTLR (0.8%), Shell (0.4%), Lua (0.2%), SCSS (0.2%), Kotlin, Batchfile, Python, TSQL, Dockerfile, Go Template\n- License: Apache License 2.0 (Apache-2.0)\n- Topics: at, consistency, distributed-transaction, microservice, saga, tcc, xa\n- Default branch: 2.x\n- Homepage: https://seata.apache.org/\n- Created: 2018-12-28T08:37:22Z\n- Last push: 2026-04-08T01:16:41Z\n- Contributors: 380 (top: slievrly, funky-eyes, xingfudeshi, wangliang181230, jsbxyyx, l81893521, Bughue, zjinlei, sharajava, caohdgege)\n- Releases: 45\n- Latest release: v2.6.0 (2026-01-28T15:55:30Z)\n[...]\nYou can view the full documentation from Apache Seata Official Website: Apache Seata Website page.\n[...]\n- Apache Seata Website - Apache Seata official website\n- Apache Seata GoLang - Apache Seata GoLang client\n- Apache Seata Samples - Samples for Apache Seata Java\n- Apache Seata GoLang Samples - Samples for Apache Seata GoLang\n- Apache Seata K8s - Apache Seata integration with Kubernetes\n- Apache Seata CLI - CLI tool for Apache Seata operations\n\n---\n\nTitle: Apollo Configuration Center | Apache Seata\nURL: https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/configuration/apollo\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApollo Configuration Center | Apache Seata\n[...]\nVersion: v2.6\n[...]\n# Apollo Configuration Center\n[...]\nThe steps to integrate Seata with the Apollo Configuration Center are very simple and can be roughly divided into \"Adding Maven Dependencies\" and\n[...]\nconfiguration to Apollo-Server\".\n[...]\n### Upload Configuration to\n[...]\nConfiguration Center‚Äč\n[...]\nRefer to config.txt in https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/tree/develop/script/config-center and make modifications. Then run the provided Apollo script in the repository to submit the information to the Apollo console. If there is a need for changes, they can be directly made through the console.\n\n---\n\nTitle: apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website\nPublished: 2019-01-18T13:04:50.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nApache Seata(incubating) Website\n[...]\n- Stars: 108\n- Forks: 134\n- Watchers: 108\n- Open issues: 27\n- Primary language: JavaScript\n- Languages: JavaScript (45.1%), SCSS (22.1%), TypeScript (19.4%), HTML (12.6%), CSS (0.5%), Shell (0.4%)\n- License: Apache License 2.0 (Apache-2.0)\n- Topics: article, distributed-transaction, docsite, seata-website\n- Default branch: docusaurus\n- Homepage: https://seata.apache.org/\n- Created: 2019-01-18T13:04:50Z\n- Last push: 2026-03-17T00:31:59Z\n- Contributors: 100 (top: slievrly, funky-eyes, lovepoem, liuqiufeng, zjinlei, chai001125, xingfudeshi, lightClouds917, lvekee, l81893521)\n[...]\n# Seata Official Website\n[...]\nseata website deploy on github\n[...]\nAll website material of https://seata.apache.org, which uses a open source framework: Docusaurus."},"obs_mpyl9yke_968e0d7d4372":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpyl9yke_968e0d7d4372","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_9b919a8c3452475eae9a1239","duration_ms":5517,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","tool_input":"{\"query\":\"Seata 2.6.0 Docker deployment Nacos registry configuration\",\"numResults\":5}","tool_name":"websearch_web_search_exa","tool_output":"Title: i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose-142.md at docusaurus ¬∑ apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose-142.md\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n<a href=\"#file-file\n[...]\nRegistration Center, File Storage</a>\n[...]\n<a href=\"#\n[...]\n-db\">\n[...]\nRegistration Center, db Storage</a>\n* <\n[...]\nhref=\"#nacos-\n[...]\nNacos Registration Center, db Storage</a>\n* <a href=\"#\n[...]\n-nacos-db\">High Available Usage Deployment</a>\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n[...]\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\nDirect connection mode (no registration center)\n[...]\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"file\"\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"file\"\n  \n   file {\n     name=\"file:/root/seata-config/file.conf\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.1\"\n[...]\nservices:\n   seata-server:\n     image: seataio/seata\n[...]\n-version}\n[...]\nhostname: seata\n[...]\nports:\n       - \"8091:8091\"\n[...]\nenvironment:\n       - SEATA_PORT=80\n[...]\nCONFIG_NAME=file\n[...]\nfolder\n[...]\n\"./seata\n[...]\nserver/config:/root/seata\n[...]\n### Nacos Registration Center, db Storage \n\n> The db mode needs to create the corresponding table structure in the database, please refer to [table creation script].\n[...]\n**(1) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n\nNacos Registration Center.\n\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n   # The alias the seata service is registered on nacos, and the client calls the service through this alias.\n     application = \"seata-server\"\n   # Please configure the IP and port of the nacos service according to the actual production environment.\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n   # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     cluster = \"default\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   }\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n     # Please configure the IP and port of the nacos service according to the actual production environment.\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n     # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     group = \"SEATA_GROUP\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   # Starting from v1.4.2, it has been supported to obtain all configuration information from one Nacos dataId. You only need to add an additional dataId configuration item.\n     dataId: \"seataServer.properties\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare nacos configuration center configuration**\n\nFor more storage mode support, please refer to More storage modes.\n\n> You need to create a new configuration in nacos, where the dataId is seataServer.properties\n[...]\n```properties\n# Storage mode\nstore.mode=db\n\nstore.db.datasource=druid\nstore.db.dbType=mysql\n[...]\n# Need to adjust driver\n[...]\naccording to mysql version\n#\n[...]\ncorresponding to mysql\n[...]\nand above versions is: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver\n# Driver for versions below mysql8 is: com.mysql.jdbc.Driver\nstore.db.driverClassName=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver\n[...]\n# Pay attention to adjusting the parameters host and port according to the\n[...]\nsituation.\nstore.db.url=jdbc:mysql://127.0.0.1:3306/seata-server?useUnicode=true&characterEncoding=utf8&connectTimeout=1000&socketTimeout=3000&autoReconnect=true&useSSL=false\n[...]\n# database username\nstore.db.user= \"usernanme\"\n[...]\n# Username Password\nstore.db.password= \"password\"\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.1\"\nservices:\n   seata-server:\n     image: seataio/seata-server:${latest-release-version}\n     hostname: seata-server\n     ports:\n       - \"8091:8091\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=8091\n       # Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The client will access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network IP.\n       - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # Because registry.conf is the nacos configuration center, you only need to put registry.conf in the ./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n```\n[...]\n**(1) Prepare\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n[...]\nNacos registration center.\n\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n   # The alias the seata service is registered on nacos, and the client calls the service through this alias.\n     application = \"seata-server\"\n   #IP and port of nacos service\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n   # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     cluster = \"default\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   }\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"file\"\n  \n   file {\n     name=\"file:/root/seata-config/file.conf\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\nversion: \"3\n[...]\nservices:\n   #se\n[...]\nimage: se\n[...]\nserver:${latest\n[...]\nhostname: se\n[...]\nserver\n     ports:\n       - \"8091:80\n[...]\n1\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=80\n[...]\n# Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The\n[...]\nwill access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network IP.\n       - SEATA\n[...]\nIP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # You need to put both file.conf and registry.conf in\n[...]\n./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n   #\n[...]\naservice2\n   seata-server-2:\n     image: seataio/seata-server:${latest\n[...]\nrelease-version}\n     hostname: seata-server\n     ports:\n       - \"8092:8092\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=8092\n       # Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The\n[...]\nwill access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network\n[...]\n.\n       - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # You need to put both file.conf and registry.conf in the ./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n  \n   #\n[...]\n3......\n[...]\n- **STORE_MODE**\n[...]\n- **SE\n[...]\n> Optional. It is\n[...]\nthe seata-\n[...]\n, such as `dev`, `test`, etc\n[...]\nthe service is\n[...]\n, configurations such as `registry-dev.conf` will be used.\n[...]\n- **SEATA_CONFIG_NAME**\n\n> Optional. It is used to specify the configuration file location, such as `file:/root/registry`, which will load `/root/registry.conf` as the configuration file. If you need to specify the `file.conf` file at the same time, you need to change the value of `config.file.name` in `registry.conf` to something like `file:/root/file.conf`.\n\n---\n\nTitle: i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md at docusaurus ¬∑ apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n# Nacos Registry\n[...]\nNacos is an important registry implementation in the Seata component.\n[...]\nBefore integrating `nacos-client` into your Seata project, make sure that the Nacos service is already running in the background. If you are not familiar with the basic usage of Nacos, you can refer to the Nacos Quick Start guide. It is recommended to use Nacos version `1.4.0` or above.\n[...]\nThe steps to integ"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:15.050Z","toolInput":"{\"query\":\"Seata 2.6.0 Docker deployment Nacos registry configuration\",\"numResults\":5}","toolName":"websearch_web_search_exa","toolOutput":"Title: i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose-142.md at docusaurus ¬∑ apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose-142.md\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n<a href=\"#file-file\n[...]\nRegistration Center, File Storage</a>\n[...]\n<a href=\"#\n[...]\n-db\">\n[...]\nRegistration Center, db Storage</a>\n* <\n[...]\nhref=\"#nacos-\n[...]\nNacos Registration Center, db Storage</a>\n* <a href=\"#\n[...]\n-nacos-db\">High Available Usage Deployment</a>\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n[...]\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\nDirect connection mode (no registration center)\n[...]\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"file\"\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"file\"\n  \n   file {\n     name=\"file:/root/seata-config/file.conf\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.1\"\n[...]\nservices:\n   seata-server:\n     image: seataio/seata\n[...]\n-version}\n[...]\nhostname: seata\n[...]\nports:\n       - \"8091:8091\"\n[...]\nenvironment:\n       - SEATA_PORT=80\n[...]\nCONFIG_NAME=file\n[...]\nfolder\n[...]\n\"./seata\n[...]\nserver/config:/root/seata\n[...]\n### Nacos Registration Center, db Storage \n\n> The db mode needs to create the corresponding table structure in the database, please refer to [table creation script].\n[...]\n**(1) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n\nNacos Registration Center.\n\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n   # The alias the seata service is registered on nacos, and the client calls the service through this alias.\n     application = \"seata-server\"\n   # Please configure the IP and port of the nacos service according to the actual production environment.\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n   # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     cluster = \"default\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   }\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n     # Please configure the IP and port of the nacos service according to the actual production environment.\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n     # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     group = \"SEATA_GROUP\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   # Starting from v1.4.2, it has been supported to obtain all configuration information from one Nacos dataId. You only need to add an additional dataId configuration item.\n     dataId: \"seataServer.properties\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare nacos configuration center configuration**\n\nFor more storage mode support, please refer to More storage modes.\n\n> You need to create a new configuration in nacos, where the dataId is seataServer.properties\n[...]\n```properties\n# Storage mode\nstore.mode=db\n\nstore.db.datasource=druid\nstore.db.dbType=mysql\n[...]\n# Need to adjust driver\n[...]\naccording to mysql version\n#\n[...]\ncorresponding to mysql\n[...]\nand above versions is: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver\n# Driver for versions below mysql8 is: com.mysql.jdbc.Driver\nstore.db.driverClassName=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver\n[...]\n# Pay attention to adjusting the parameters host and port according to the\n[...]\nsituation.\nstore.db.url=jdbc:mysql://127.0.0.1:3306/seata-server?useUnicode=true&characterEncoding=utf8&connectTimeout=1000&socketTimeout=3000&autoReconnect=true&useSSL=false\n[...]\n# database username\nstore.db.user= \"usernanme\"\n[...]\n# Username Password\nstore.db.password= \"password\"\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.1\"\nservices:\n   seata-server:\n     image: seataio/seata-server:${latest-release-version}\n     hostname: seata-server\n     ports:\n       - \"8091:8091\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=8091\n       # Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The client will access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network IP.\n       - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # Because registry.conf is the nacos configuration center, you only need to put registry.conf in the ./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n```\n[...]\n**(1) Prepare\n[...]\n**(2) Prepare file: registry.conf**\n[...]\nNacos registration center.\n\nFor more registration center support, please refer to Registration Center \n\nFor more configuration center support, please refer to Configuration Center \n\n```\nregistry {\n   type = \"nacos\"\n  \n   nacos {\n   # The alias the seata service is registered on nacos, and the client calls the service through this alias.\n     application = \"seata-server\"\n   #IP and port of nacos service\n     serverAddr = \"127.0.0.1:8848\"\n   # The namespace specified on nacos\n     namespace = \"\"\n     cluster = \"default\"\n     username = \"nacos\"\n     password = \"nacos\"\n   }\n}\n\nconfig {\n   type = \"file\"\n  \n   file {\n     name=\"file:/root/seata-config/file.conf\"\n   }\n}\n```\n[...]\n**(3) Prepare file: docker-compose.yaml**\n[...]\nversion: \"3\n[...]\nservices:\n   #se\n[...]\nimage: se\n[...]\nserver:${latest\n[...]\nhostname: se\n[...]\nserver\n     ports:\n       - \"8091:80\n[...]\n1\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=80\n[...]\n# Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The\n[...]\nwill access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network IP.\n       - SEATA\n[...]\nIP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # You need to put both file.conf and registry.conf in\n[...]\n./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n   #\n[...]\naservice2\n   seata-server-2:\n     image: seataio/seata-server:${latest\n[...]\nrelease-version}\n     hostname: seata-server\n     ports:\n       - \"8092:8092\"\n     environment:\n       # Specify the seata service startup port\n       - SEATA_PORT=8092\n       # Specify the Ip registered to nacos. The\n[...]\nwill access the seata service through this IP.\n       # Pay attention to the difference between public network IP and internal network\n[...]\n.\n       - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n       - SEATA_CONFIG_NAME=file:/root/seata-config/registry\n     volumes:\n     # You need to put both file.conf and registry.conf in the ./seata-server/config folder\n       - \"./seata-server/config:/root/seata-config\"\n  \n   #\n[...]\n3......\n[...]\n- **STORE_MODE**\n[...]\n- **SE\n[...]\n> Optional. It is\n[...]\nthe seata-\n[...]\n, such as `dev`, `test`, etc\n[...]\nthe service is\n[...]\n, configurations such as `registry-dev.conf` will be used.\n[...]\n- **SEATA_CONFIG_NAME**\n\n> Optional. It is used to specify the configuration file location, such as `file:/root/registry`, which will load `/root/registry.conf` as the configuration file. If you need to specify the `file.conf` file at the same time, you need to change the value of `config.file.name` in `registry.conf` to something like `file:/root/file.conf`.\n\n---\n\nTitle: i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md at docusaurus ¬∑ apache/incubator-seata-website\nURL: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n# Nacos Registry\n[...]\nNacos is an important registry implementation in the Seata component.\n[...]\nBefore integrating `nacos-client` into your Seata project, make sure that the Nacos service is already running in the background. If you are not familiar with the basic usage of Nacos, you can refer to the Nacos Quick Start guide. It is recommended to use Nacos version `1.4.0` or above.\n[...]\nThe steps to integ"},"obs_mpyla50k_69084d6c9d33":{"hookType":"step_finish","id":"obs_mpyla50k_69084d6c9d33","raw":{"cost":0,"input_tokens":32452,"messageID":"msg_e8f6cd7d9001vnKA2OEMppHt1W","output_tokens":160,"reason":"tool-calls","reasoning_tokens":151},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:23.489Z"},"obs_mpyla51d_f5e5cc312e44":{"hookType":"patch_applied","id":"obs_mpyla51d_f5e5cc312e44","raw":{"files":["/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/state_store.db/mem%3Ahealth.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/state_store.db/mem%3Ametrics.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/state_store.db/mem%3Aobs%3Ases_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/state_store.db/mem%3Aobs%3Ases_170cc99cbffeoXofytUiKB6L9o.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/state_store.db/mem%3Asessions.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/stream_store/stream%3Amem-live%3Ases_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu.bin","/home/administrator/BeibuMall/data/stream_store/stream%3Amem-live%3Ases_170cc99cbffeoXofytUiKB6L9o.bin"],"hash":"8ebc5e7695facecd9aa3c1ec68e30b4382e8a20c","messageID":"msg_e8f6cd7d9001vnKA2OEMppHt1W"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:23.518Z"},"obs_mpylai5u_519760c6980e":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpylai5u_519760c6980e","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_46934ae93ea543ba8fb8a70b","duration_ms":6066,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","tool_input":"{\"libraryId\":\"/apache/incubator-seata\",\"query\":\"Spring Boot 3 application.yml configuration seata registry nacos starter\"}","tool_name":"context7_query-docs","tool_output":"### Seata Application Configuration\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nThis YAML snippet configures Seata's core settings, including enabling distributed transactions, setting application IDs, transaction service groups, and data source proxy modes. It also details client-side configurations for resource managers (RM) and transaction managers (TM), undo log settings, registry (Nacos example), config center (Nacos example), and specific configurations for TCC and Saga modes.\n\n```yaml\nseata:\n  enabled: true\n  application-id: ${spring.application.name}\n  tx-service-group: default_tx_group\n  enable-auto-data-source-proxy: true\n  data-source-proxy-mode: AT  # AT or XA\n\n  client:\n    rm:\n      async-commit-buffer-limit: 10000\n      report-retry-count: 5\n      table-meta-check-enable: true\n      lock:\n        retry-interval: 10\n        retry-times: 30\n        retry-policy-branch-rollback-on-conflict: true\n    tm:\n      commit-retry-count: 5\n      rollback-retry-count: 5\n      default-global-transaction-timeout: 60000\n      degrade-check: false\n      degrade-check-period: 2000\n      degrade-check-allow-times: 10\n    undo:\n      data-validation: true\n      log-serialization: jackson\n      log-table: undo_log\n      only-care-update-columns: true\n      compress:\n        enable: true\n        type: zip\n        threshold: 64k\n\n  service:\n    vgroup-mapping:\n      default_tx_group: default\n    grouplist:\n      default: 127.0.0.1:8091\n    disable-global-transaction: false\n\n  # Registry configuration (Nacos example)\n  registry:\n    type: nacos\n    nacos:\n      application: seata-server\n      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848\n      group: SEATA_GROUP\n      namespace: public\n      username: nacos\n      password: nacos\n\n  # Config center configuration\n  config:\n    type: nacos\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848\n      group: SEATA_GROUP\n      namespace: public\n      data-id: seata.properties\n      username: nacos\n      password: nacos\n\n  # TCC specific configuration\n  tcc:\n    fence:\n      log-table-name: tcc_fence_log\n      clean-period: 1h\n    context-json-parser-type: jackson\n\n  # Saga specific configuration\n  saga:\n    enabled: true\n    state-machine:\n      table-prefix: seata_\n      enable-async: false\n      trans-operation-timeout: 1800000\n      service-invoke-timeout: 300000\n      auto-register-resources: true\n      resources:\n        - classpath*:seata/saga/statelang/**/*.json\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Add Seata Spring Boot Starter Dependency\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nInclude this dependency in your pom.xml to enable Seata's distributed transaction support within a Spring Boot environment. Ensure the seata.version property is set to the desired Seata release.\n\n```xml\n<properties>\n    <seata.version>2.5.0</seata.version>\n</properties>\n\n<dependencies>\n    <!-- Seata Spring Boot Starter (recommended) -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>org.apache.seata</groupId>\n        <artifactId>seata-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n        <version>${seata.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Alternative: seata-all for non-Spring Boot applications -->\n    <!--\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>org.apache.seata</groupId>\n        <artifactId>seata-all</artifactId>\n        <version>${seata.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    -->\n\n    <!-- MySQL driver for AT mode undo_log -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>mysql</groupId>\n        <artifactId>mysql-connector-java</artifactId>\n        <version>8.0.33</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Druid for connection pooling (recommended) -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>com.alibaba</groupId>\n        <artifactId>druid-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n        <version>1.2.18</version>\n    </dependency>\n</dependencies>\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Seata Naming Server Application Configuration\n\nSource: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/distribution/NOTICE.md\n\nMain application configuration file for Seata Naming Server. This YAML file defines server properties, registry, and configuration center settings.\n\n```yaml\nserver:\n  port: 8091\n\nseata:\n  # Enable Naming Server\n  enable-naming-server: true\n  # Naming service address\n  naming-service-address: \"localhost:8848\"\n  # Registry type: nacos, zk, redis, etcd3, consul\n  registry:\n    type: \"nacos\"\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: \"localhost:8848\"\n      namespace: \"public\"\n      username: \"\"\n      password: \"\"\n  # Configuration center type: nacos, zk, apollo, consul, etcd3\n  config:\n    type: \"nacos\"\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: \"localhost:8848\"\n      namespace: \"public\"\n      username: \"\"\n      password: \"\"\n  # Log configuration\n  log:\n    file:\n      path: \"logs/seata-namingserver.log\"\n    level: \"info\"\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Docker Compose for Seata Server Deployment\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nA Docker Compose configuration to deploy Seata Server along with its dependencies (MySQL, Nacos) for development and testing. This setup uses the latest Seata Server image and configures storage mode to 'db'.\n\n```yaml\n# docker-compose.yaml\nversion: \"3\" \nservices:\n  seata-server:\n    image: seataio/seata-server:latest\n    hostname: seata-server\n    ports:\n      - \"8091:8091\"\n      - \"7091:7091\"\n    environment:\n      - SEATA_PORT=8091\n      - STORE_MODE=db\n      - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n    volumes:\n      - ./seata-server/resources:/seata-server/resources\n    depends_on:\n      - mysql\n      - nacos\n\n  mysql:\n    image: mysql:8.0\n    ports:\n      - \"3306:3306\"\n    environment:\n      - MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root\n      - MYSQL_DATABASE=seata\n    volumes:\n      - ./mysql/init:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d\n\n  nacos:\n    image: nacos/nacos-server:latest\n    ports:\n      - \"8848:8848\"\n    environment:\n      - MODE=standalone\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Registry Configuration Examples\n\nSource: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/wiki/ctl-survey\n\nConfiguration examples for different service registries like Eureka and Nacos. Use -r and -a to specify the registry and application name for cluster operations.\n\n```ini\n[registry-1]\ntype=eureka\nservice-url=http://localhost:8761/eureka\n\n[registry-2]\ntype=nacos\nserver-addr=127.0.0.1:8848\ngroup=\"SEATA_GROUP\"\nnamespace=\"\"\nusername=\"nacos\"\npassword=\"nacos\"\n\n...\n```"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:40.523Z","toolInput":"{\"libraryId\":\"/apache/incubator-seata\",\"query\":\"Spring Boot 3 application.yml configuration seata registry nacos starter\"}","toolName":"context7_query-docs","toolOutput":"### Seata Application Configuration\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nThis YAML snippet configures Seata's core settings, including enabling distributed transactions, setting application IDs, transaction service groups, and data source proxy modes. It also details client-side configurations for resource managers (RM) and transaction managers (TM), undo log settings, registry (Nacos example), config center (Nacos example), and specific configurations for TCC and Saga modes.\n\n```yaml\nseata:\n  enabled: true\n  application-id: ${spring.application.name}\n  tx-service-group: default_tx_group\n  enable-auto-data-source-proxy: true\n  data-source-proxy-mode: AT  # AT or XA\n\n  client:\n    rm:\n      async-commit-buffer-limit: 10000\n      report-retry-count: 5\n      table-meta-check-enable: true\n      lock:\n        retry-interval: 10\n        retry-times: 30\n        retry-policy-branch-rollback-on-conflict: true\n    tm:\n      commit-retry-count: 5\n      rollback-retry-count: 5\n      default-global-transaction-timeout: 60000\n      degrade-check: false\n      degrade-check-period: 2000\n      degrade-check-allow-times: 10\n    undo:\n      data-validation: true\n      log-serialization: jackson\n      log-table: undo_log\n      only-care-update-columns: true\n      compress:\n        enable: true\n        type: zip\n        threshold: 64k\n\n  service:\n    vgroup-mapping:\n      default_tx_group: default\n    grouplist:\n      default: 127.0.0.1:8091\n    disable-global-transaction: false\n\n  # Registry configuration (Nacos example)\n  registry:\n    type: nacos\n    nacos:\n      application: seata-server\n      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848\n      group: SEATA_GROUP\n      namespace: public\n      username: nacos\n      password: nacos\n\n  # Config center configuration\n  config:\n    type: nacos\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848\n      group: SEATA_GROUP\n      namespace: public\n      data-id: seata.properties\n      username: nacos\n      password: nacos\n\n  # TCC specific configuration\n  tcc:\n    fence:\n      log-table-name: tcc_fence_log\n      clean-period: 1h\n    context-json-parser-type: jackson\n\n  # Saga specific configuration\n  saga:\n    enabled: true\n    state-machine:\n      table-prefix: seata_\n      enable-async: false\n      trans-operation-timeout: 1800000\n      service-invoke-timeout: 300000\n      auto-register-resources: true\n      resources:\n        - classpath*:seata/saga/statelang/**/*.json\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Add Seata Spring Boot Starter Dependency\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nInclude this dependency in your pom.xml to enable Seata's distributed transaction support within a Spring Boot environment. Ensure the seata.version property is set to the desired Seata release.\n\n```xml\n<properties>\n    <seata.version>2.5.0</seata.version>\n</properties>\n\n<dependencies>\n    <!-- Seata Spring Boot Starter (recommended) -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>org.apache.seata</groupId>\n        <artifactId>seata-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n        <version>${seata.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Alternative: seata-all for non-Spring Boot applications -->\n    <!--\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>org.apache.seata</groupId>\n        <artifactId>seata-all</artifactId>\n        <version>${seata.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    -->\n\n    <!-- MySQL driver for AT mode undo_log -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>mysql</groupId>\n        <artifactId>mysql-connector-java</artifactId>\n        <version>8.0.33</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Druid for connection pooling (recommended) -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>com.alibaba</groupId>\n        <artifactId>druid-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n        <version>1.2.18</version>\n    </dependency>\n</dependencies>\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Seata Naming Server Application Configuration\n\nSource: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/distribution/NOTICE.md\n\nMain application configuration file for Seata Naming Server. This YAML file defines server properties, registry, and configuration center settings.\n\n```yaml\nserver:\n  port: 8091\n\nseata:\n  # Enable Naming Server\n  enable-naming-server: true\n  # Naming service address\n  naming-service-address: \"localhost:8848\"\n  # Registry type: nacos, zk, redis, etcd3, consul\n  registry:\n    type: \"nacos\"\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: \"localhost:8848\"\n      namespace: \"public\"\n      username: \"\"\n      password: \"\"\n  # Configuration center type: nacos, zk, apollo, consul, etcd3\n  config:\n    type: \"nacos\"\n    nacos:\n      server-addr: \"localhost:8848\"\n      namespace: \"public\"\n      username: \"\"\n      password: \"\"\n  # Log configuration\n  log:\n    file:\n      path: \"logs/seata-namingserver.log\"\n    level: \"info\"\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Docker Compose for Seata Server Deployment\n\nSource: https://context7.com/apache/incubator-seata/llms.txt\n\nA Docker Compose configuration to deploy Seata Server along with its dependencies (MySQL, Nacos) for development and testing. This setup uses the latest Seata Server image and configures storage mode to 'db'.\n\n```yaml\n# docker-compose.yaml\nversion: \"3\" \nservices:\n  seata-server:\n    image: seataio/seata-server:latest\n    hostname: seata-server\n    ports:\n      - \"8091:8091\"\n      - \"7091:7091\"\n    environment:\n      - SEATA_PORT=8091\n      - STORE_MODE=db\n      - SEATA_IP=127.0.0.1\n    volumes:\n      - ./seata-server/resources:/seata-server/resources\n    depends_on:\n      - mysql\n      - nacos\n\n  mysql:\n    image: mysql:8.0\n    ports:\n      - \"3306:3306\"\n    environment:\n      - MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root\n      - MYSQL_DATABASE=seata\n    volumes:\n      - ./mysql/init:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d\n\n  nacos:\n    image: nacos/nacos-server:latest\n    ports:\n      - \"8848:8848\"\n    environment:\n      - MODE=standalone\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Registry Configuration Examples\n\nSource: https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/wiki/ctl-survey\n\nConfiguration examples for different service registries like Eureka and Nacos. Use -r and -a to specify the registry and application name for cluster operations.\n\n```ini\n[registry-1]\ntype=eureka\nservice-url=http://localhost:8761/eureka\n\n[registry-2]\ntype=nacos\nserver-addr=127.0.0.1:8848\ngroup=\"SEATA_GROUP\"\nnamespace=\"\"\nusername=\"nacos\"\npassword=\"nacos\"\n\n...\n```"},"obs_mpylaqdh_584f253fe6be":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpylaqdh_584f253fe6be","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_bee6b8c67a534a3aab17c9bf","duration_ms":16697,"metadata":{"outputPath":"/home/administrator/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e8f6d97ab001Bm6TRlnYN22d1N","truncated":true},"title":"https://seata.apache.org/sitemap.xml (application/xml)","tool_input":"{\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/sitemap.xml\",\"format\":\"text\"}","tool_name":"webfetch","tool_output":"\n\n...453816 bytes truncated...\n\nThe tool call succeeded but the output was truncated. Full output saved to: /home/administrator/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e8f6d97ab001Bm6TRlnYN22d1N\nUse Grep to search the full content or Read with offset/limit to view specific sections."},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:51.170Z","toolInput":"{\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/sitemap.xml\",\"format\":\"text\"}","toolName":"webfetch","toolOutput":"\n\n...453816 bytes truncated...\n\nThe tool call succeeded but the output was truncated. Full output saved to: /home/administrator/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e8f6d97ab001Bm6TRlnYN22d1N\nUse Grep to search the full content or Read with offset/limit to view specific sections."},"obs_mpylarwd_9101115d8690":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpylarwd_9101115d8690","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_b98b5c8d63c2423ba309232f","duration_ms":18712,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/registry/nacos (text/html)","tool_input":"{\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/registry/nacos\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}","tool_name":"webfetch","tool_output":"  Nacos Registry Center | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/user/registry/nacos)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n        -   [Introduction](/docs/user/registry/)\n        -   [Nacos Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n        -   [Eureka Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/eureka)\n        -   [Etcd3 Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/etcd3)\n        -   [Consul Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/consul)\n        -   [Zookeeper Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/zookeeper)\n        -   [Seata Namingserver Registry](/docs/user/registry/namingserver)\n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   User Doc\n-   Registry Center\n-   Nacos Registry Center\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\nOn this page\n\n# Nacos Registry\n\nNacos is an important registry implementation in the Seata component.\n\n## Prerequisites[‚Äč](#prerequisites \"Direct link to Prerequisites\")\n\nBefore integrating `nacos-client` into your Seata project, make sure that the Nacos service is already running in the background. If you are not familiar with the basic usage of Nacos, you can refer to the [Nacos Quick Start](https://nacos.io/en-us/docs/quick-start.html) guide. It is recommended to use Nacos version `1.4.0` or above.\n\n## Quick Start[‚Äč](#quick-start \"Direct link to Quick Start\")\n\nThe steps to integrate Nacos registry into Seata are very simple and can be roughly divided into \"adding Maven dependencies\" and \"configuring the registry\".\n\n### Adding Maven Dependencies[‚Äč](#adding-maven-dependencies \"Direct link to Adding Maven Dependencies\")\n\nFirst, you need to add the Maven dependency for `nacos-client` to your project's `pom.xml` file.\n\n```\n<dependency>    <groupId>io.seata</groupId>    <artifactId>seata-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>    <version>latest version</version></dependency><dependency>    <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>    <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>    <version>1.4.0+</version></dependency>\n```\n\n### Configuring the Registry on the Client Side[‚Äč](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-client-side \"Direct link to Configuring the Registry on the Client Side\")\n\nAdd the corresponding configuration to [**application.yml**](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/script/client/spring/application.yml):\n\n```\nseata:  registry:    type: nacos    nacos:      application: seata-server      namespace: \"\"      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848      group: SEATA_GROUP      username: \"\"      password: \"\"      ##if use MSE Nacos with auth, mutex with username/password attribute      #access-key: \"\"      #secret-key: \"\"      data-id: seata.properties  tx-service-group: default_tx_group  service:    vgroup-mapping:      default_tx_group: default\n```\n\n### Configuring the Registry on the Server Side[‚Äč](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-server-side \"Direct link to Configuring the Registry on the Server Side\")\n\nAdd the corresponding configuration to `conf/application.yaml`, and refer to other [configuration options](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml):\n\n```\nseata:  registry:    type: nacos    nacos:      application: seata-server      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848      group: SEATA_GROUP      namespace:      cluster: default      username:      password:      ##if use MSE Nacos with auth, mutex with username/password attribute      #access-key: \"\"      #secret-key: \"\"\n```\n\nAfter that, when you start the Seata-Server, you will see the server's service appearing in the registry list on the Nacos console. Once the client is configured, you can start the application to experience the Seata service.\n\nTips: Make sure that the client and server are registered in the same namespace and group, otherwise the service will not be found.\n\n[Edit this page](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md)\n\n[\n\nPrevious\n\nIntroduction\n\n](/docs/user/registry/)[\n\nNext\n\nEureka Registry Center\n\n](/docs/user/registry/eureka)\n\n-   [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)\n-   [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n    -   [Adding Maven Dependencies](#adding-maven-dependencies)\n    -   [Configuring the Registry on the Client Side](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-client-side)\n    -   [Configuring the Registry on the Server Side](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-server-side)\n\n[![Apache Incubator Logo](/img/apache/incubator.svg)![Apache Incubator Logo](/img/apache/incubator.svg)](https://incubator.apache.org/)\n\nApache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) is an effort undergoing incubation at The Apache Software Foundation (ASF), sponsored by the Apache Incubator. Incubation is required of all newly accepted projects until a further review indicates that the infrastructure, communications, and decision making process have stabilized in a manner consistent with other successful ASF"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:39:53.146Z","toolInput":"{\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/registry/nacos\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}","toolName":"webfetch","toolOutput":"  Nacos Registry Center | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/user/registry/nacos)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n        -   [Introduction](/docs/user/registry/)\n        -   [Nacos Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/nacos)\n        -   [Eureka Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/eureka)\n        -   [Etcd3 Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/etcd3)\n        -   [Consul Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/consul)\n        -   [Zookeeper Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/zookeeper)\n        -   [Seata Namingserver Registry](/docs/user/registry/namingserver)\n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   User Doc\n-   Registry Center\n-   Nacos Registry Center\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\nOn this page\n\n# Nacos Registry\n\nNacos is an important registry implementation in the Seata component.\n\n## Prerequisites[‚Äč](#prerequisites \"Direct link to Prerequisites\")\n\nBefore integrating `nacos-client` into your Seata project, make sure that the Nacos service is already running in the background. If you are not familiar with the basic usage of Nacos, you can refer to the [Nacos Quick Start](https://nacos.io/en-us/docs/quick-start.html) guide. It is recommended to use Nacos version `1.4.0` or above.\n\n## Quick Start[‚Äč](#quick-start \"Direct link to Quick Start\")\n\nThe steps to integrate Nacos registry into Seata are very simple and can be roughly divided into \"adding Maven dependencies\" and \"configuring the registry\".\n\n### Adding Maven Dependencies[‚Äč](#adding-maven-dependencies \"Direct link to Adding Maven Dependencies\")\n\nFirst, you need to add the Maven dependency for `nacos-client` to your project's `pom.xml` file.\n\n```\n<dependency>    <groupId>io.seata</groupId>    <artifactId>seata-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>    <version>latest version</version></dependency><dependency>    <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>    <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>    <version>1.4.0+</version></dependency>\n```\n\n### Configuring the Registry on the Client Side[‚Äč](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-client-side \"Direct link to Configuring the Registry on the Client Side\")\n\nAdd the corresponding configuration to [**application.yml**](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/script/client/spring/application.yml):\n\n```\nseata:  registry:    type: nacos    nacos:      application: seata-server      namespace: \"\"      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848      group: SEATA_GROUP      username: \"\"      password: \"\"      ##if use MSE Nacos with auth, mutex with username/password attribute      #access-key: \"\"      #secret-key: \"\"      data-id: seata.properties  tx-service-group: default_tx_group  service:    vgroup-mapping:      default_tx_group: default\n```\n\n### Configuring the Registry on the Server Side[‚Äč](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-server-side \"Direct link to Configuring the Registry on the Server Side\")\n\nAdd the corresponding configuration to `conf/application.yaml`, and refer to other [configuration options](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/2.x/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml):\n\n```\nseata:  registry:    type: nacos    nacos:      application: seata-server      server-addr: 127.0.0.1:8848      group: SEATA_GROUP      namespace:      cluster: default      username:      password:      ##if use MSE Nacos with auth, mutex with username/password attribute      #access-key: \"\"      #secret-key: \"\"\n```\n\nAfter that, when you start the Seata-Server, you will see the server's service appearing in the registry list on the Nacos console. Once the client is configured, you can start the application to experience the Seata service.\n\nTips: Make sure that the client and server are registered in the same namespace and group, otherwise the service will not be found.\n\n[Edit this page](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata-website/blob/docusaurus/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/version-v2.6/user/registry/nacos.md)\n\n[\n\nPrevious\n\nIntroduction\n\n](/docs/user/registry/)[\n\nNext\n\nEureka Registry Center\n\n](/docs/user/registry/eureka)\n\n-   [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)\n-   [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n    -   [Adding Maven Dependencies](#adding-maven-dependencies)\n    -   [Configuring the Registry on the Client Side](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-client-side)\n    -   [Configuring the Registry on the Server Side](#configuring-the-registry-on-the-server-side)\n\n[![Apache Incubator Logo](/img/apache/incubator.svg)![Apache Incubator Logo](/img/apache/incubator.svg)](https://incubator.apache.org/)\n\nApache Seata‚ĄĘ (incubating) is an effort undergoing incubation at The Apache Software Foundation (ASF), sponsored by the Apache Incubator. Incubation is required of all newly accepted projects until a further review indicates that the infrastructure, communications, and decision making process have stabilized in a manner consistent with other successful ASF"},"obs_mpylb9sm_ff4ae48d9c93":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpylb9sm_ff4ae48d9c93","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_d47cfb6ffe98420b8ac21313","duration_ms":14181,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://seata.apache.org/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose/ (text/html)","tool_input":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose/\"}","tool_name":"webfetch","tool_output":"  Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n        -   [Beginner Deployment Guide](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        -   [Deploy Server](/docs/ops/deploy-server)\n        -   [Deploying Raft Cluster](/docs/ops/deploy-server-raft)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Docker](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n        -   [Deploy with Kubernetes](/docs/ops/deploy-by-kubernetes)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Helm](/docs/ops/deploy-by-helm)\n        -   [High Available Usage Deployment](/docs/ops/deploy-ha)\n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   Ops Guide\n-   Deploy\n-   Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\nOn this page\n\n# Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose\n\n## Precautions[‚Äč](#precautions \"Direct link to Precautions\")\n\n-   Please avoid directly pulling the latest version image. The latest version is not necessarily a stable version. To avoid unnecessary problems, please go to [docker image warehouse](https://hub.docker.com/r/apache/seata-server/tags) to determine the image version to be pulled.\n-   Starting from Seata Server version 1.5.0, the configuration file has been changed to application.yml. So when using custom configuration, you need to copy the native configuration first.\n\n## Use custom configuration file[‚Äč](#use-custom-configuration-file \"Direct link to Use custom configuration file\")\n\nIn order to obtain the configuration file of seata server 1.5.0, we need to first start a service of seata server 1.5.0, then copy the default configuration file from the started container instance, and then modify it.\n\ndocker-compose.yaml\n\n```\nversion: \"3.1\"services:  seata-server:    image: apache/seata-server:${latest-release-version}    ports:      - \"7091:7091\"      - \"8091:8091\"\n```\n\nNext, copy the resource file in the `/seata-server/resources` location in the container to the specified location of the host through the `docker cp` command. In the specified location of the host, we can see the corresponding `application.yml` configuration file, and the relevant configuration only needs to modify this file.\n\n> The configuration of `application.yml` can refer to [application.example.yml](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml)\n\n## Quick Start[‚Äč](#quick-start \"Direct link to Quick Start\")\n\n-   [No Registration Center, File Storage](#file-file)\n-   [No Registration Center, db Storage](#file-db)\n-   [Nacos Registration Center, db Storage](#nacos-db)\n-   [High Available Usage Deployment](#ha-nacos-db)\n\n### No Registration Center, File Storage[‚Äč](#no-registration-center-file-storage \"Direct link to no-registration-center-file-storage\")\n\nIn this mode, there is no need for a registration center or any third-party storage center.\n\ndocker-compose.yaml\n\n```\nversion: \"3.1\"services:  seata-server:    image: apache/seata-server:${latest-release-version}    hostname: seata-server    ports:      - \"7091:7091\"      - \"8091:8091\"    environment:      - SEATA_PORT=8091      - STORE_MODE=file\n```\n\n### No Registration Center, db Storage[‚Äč](#no-registration-center-db-storage \"Direct link to no-registration-center-db-storage\")\n\n> The db mode needs to create the corresponding table structure in the database, please refer to [\\[table creation script\\]](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/tree/develop/script/server/db).\n\n**Ôľą1ÔľČapplication.yml**\n\n> The configuration of `application.yml` can refer to [application.example.yml](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml)\n\nFor more storage mode support, please refer to [More Storage Modes](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/script/config-center/config.txt).\n\n```\nserver:  port: 7091spring:  application:    name: seata-serverlogging:  config: classpath:logback-spring.xml  file:    path: ${user.home}/logs/seata  extend:    logstash-appender:      destination: 127.0.0.1:4560    kafka-appender:      bootstrap-servers: 127.0.0.1:9092      topic: logback_to_logstashconsole:  user:    username: seata    password: seataseata:  config:    # support: nacos, consul, apollo, zk, etcd3    type: file  registry:    # support: nacos, eureka, redis, zk, consul, etcd3, sofa    type: file  store:    # support: file „ÄĀ db „ÄĀ redis    mode: db    db:      datasource: druid      dbType: mysql      # Need to adjust driverClassName according to mysql version      # Driver corresponding to mysql8 and above versions is: "},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:40:16.336Z","toolInput":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose/\"}","toolName":"webfetch","toolOutput":"  Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n        -   [Beginner Deployment Guide](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        -   [Deploy Server](/docs/ops/deploy-server)\n        -   [Deploying Raft Cluster](/docs/ops/deploy-server-raft)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Docker](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose](/docs/ops/deploy-by-docker-compose)\n        -   [Deploy with Kubernetes](/docs/ops/deploy-by-kubernetes)\n        -   [Deploy Seata Server By Helm](/docs/ops/deploy-by-helm)\n        -   [High Available Usage Deployment](/docs/ops/deploy-ha)\n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   Ops Guide\n-   Deploy\n-   Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\nOn this page\n\n# Deploy Seata Server By Docker Compose\n\n## Precautions[‚Äč](#precautions \"Direct link to Precautions\")\n\n-   Please avoid directly pulling the latest version image. The latest version is not necessarily a stable version. To avoid unnecessary problems, please go to [docker image warehouse](https://hub.docker.com/r/apache/seata-server/tags) to determine the image version to be pulled.\n-   Starting from Seata Server version 1.5.0, the configuration file has been changed to application.yml. So when using custom configuration, you need to copy the native configuration first.\n\n## Use custom configuration file[‚Äč](#use-custom-configuration-file \"Direct link to Use custom configuration file\")\n\nIn order to obtain the configuration file of seata server 1.5.0, we need to first start a service of seata server 1.5.0, then copy the default configuration file from the started container instance, and then modify it.\n\ndocker-compose.yaml\n\n```\nversion: \"3.1\"services:  seata-server:    image: apache/seata-server:${latest-release-version}    ports:      - \"7091:7091\"      - \"8091:8091\"\n```\n\nNext, copy the resource file in the `/seata-server/resources` location in the container to the specified location of the host through the `docker cp` command. In the specified location of the host, we can see the corresponding `application.yml` configuration file, and the relevant configuration only needs to modify this file.\n\n> The configuration of `application.yml` can refer to [application.example.yml](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml)\n\n## Quick Start[‚Äč](#quick-start \"Direct link to Quick Start\")\n\n-   [No Registration Center, File Storage](#file-file)\n-   [No Registration Center, db Storage](#file-db)\n-   [Nacos Registration Center, db Storage](#nacos-db)\n-   [High Available Usage Deployment](#ha-nacos-db)\n\n### No Registration Center, File Storage[‚Äč](#no-registration-center-file-storage \"Direct link to no-registration-center-file-storage\")\n\nIn this mode, there is no need for a registration center or any third-party storage center.\n\ndocker-compose.yaml\n\n```\nversion: \"3.1\"services:  seata-server:    image: apache/seata-server:${latest-release-version}    hostname: seata-server    ports:      - \"7091:7091\"      - \"8091:8091\"    environment:      - SEATA_PORT=8091      - STORE_MODE=file\n```\n\n### No Registration Center, db Storage[‚Äč](#no-registration-center-db-storage \"Direct link to no-registration-center-db-storage\")\n\n> The db mode needs to create the corresponding table structure in the database, please refer to [\\[table creation script\\]](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/tree/develop/script/server/db).\n\n**Ôľą1ÔľČapplication.yml**\n\n> The configuration of `application.yml` can refer to [application.example.yml](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/server/src/main/resources/application.example.yml)\n\nFor more storage mode support, please refer to [More Storage Modes](https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/blob/develop/script/config-center/config.txt).\n\n```\nserver:  port: 7091spring:  application:    name: seata-serverlogging:  config: classpath:logback-spring.xml  file:    path: ${user.home}/logs/seata  extend:    logstash-appender:      destination: 127.0.0.1:4560    kafka-appender:      bootstrap-servers: 127.0.0.1:9092      topic: logback_to_logstashconsole:  user:    username: seata    password: seataseata:  config:    # support: nacos, consul, apollo, zk, etcd3    type: file  registry:    # support: nacos, eureka, redis, zk, consul, etcd3, sofa    type: file  store:    # support: file „ÄĀ db „ÄĀ redis    mode: db    db:      datasource: druid      dbType: mysql      # Need to adjust driverClassName according to mysql version      # Driver corresponding to mysql8 and above versions is: "},"obs_mpylbb9f_f0918ec73405":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpylbb9f_f0918ec73405","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_4ab2c06d0ec54a6dab043860","duration_ms":15760,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/microservice (text/html)","tool_input":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/microservice\"}","tool_name":"webfetch","tool_output":"  Microservice Framework Guide | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/user/microservice)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/user/microservice)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/user/microservice)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   User Doc\n-   Microservice Framework Guide\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\n# Transaction Context\n\nTransaction context of Seata is managed by RootContext.\n\nWhen application begins a global transaction, RootContext will bind the XID of the transaction automatically, at the end of transaction(commit or rollback), RootContext will unbind the XID automatically.\n\n```\n// Bind XIDRootContext.bind(xid);// Unbind XIDString xid = RootContext.unbind();\n```\n\nApplication retrieve the global transaction XID through the API of RootContext.\n\n```\n// Retrieve XIDString xid = RootContext.getXID();\n```\n\nWhether application is running a global transaction, just check if an XID bound to RootContext.\n\n```\n    public static boolean inGlobalTransaction() {        return CONTEXT_HOLDER.get(KEY_XID) != null;    }\n```\n\n# Transaction propagation\n\nThe mechanism of the global transaction of Seata is the propagation of transaction context, primarily, it's the propagation way of XID in runtime.\n\n*1\\. The propagation of transaction in the service*\n\nBy default, RootContext is based on ThreadLocal, which is the XID is bound in the context of thread.\n\n```\npublic class ThreadLocalContextCore implements ContextCore {    private ThreadLocal<Map<String, String>> threadLocal = new ThreadLocal<Map<String, String>>() {        @Override        protected Map<String, String> initialValue() {            return new HashMap<String, String>();        }    };    @Override    public String put(String key, String value) {        return threadLocal.get().put(key, value);    }    @Override    public String get(String key) {        return threadLocal.get().get(key);    }    @Override    public String remove(String key) {        return threadLocal.get().remove(key);    }}\n```\n\nSo the inner XID of service is tracing by the same thread naturally, do nothing to propagate the transaction by default.\n\nIf it hopes to hung up the transaction context, implement it by the API of RootContext:\n\n```\n// Hung up(pause)String xid = RootContext.unbind();// TODO: Logic running out of the global transaction scope// recover the global transactionRootContext.bind(xid);\n```\n\n*2\\. Transactional propagation across service calls*\n\nIt's easy to know by the basic idea preceding:\n\n> The transaction propagation across service calls, essentially, propagate the XID via service call to service provider, and bind it to RootContext.\n\nAs long as it can be done, Seata can support any microservice framework in theory.\n\n# Interpretation of supporting Dubbo\n\nLet's interpret the inner support for Dubbo RPC to illustrate how Seata supports a specific microservice framework in follows:\n\nWe use the org.apache.dubbo.rpc.Filter of Dubbo to support propagation of transaction.\n\n```\n/** * The type Transaction propagation filter. */@Activate(group = { Constants.PROVIDER, Constants.CONSUMER }, order = 100)public class TransactionPropagationFilter implements Filter {    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(TransactionPropagationFilter.class);    @Override    public Result invoke(Invoker<?> invoker, Invocation invocation) throws RpcException {        String xid = RootContext.getXID(); // Get XID of current transaction        String rpcXid = RpcContext.getContext().getAttachment(RootContext.KEY_XID); // Acquire the XID from RPC invoke        if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {            LOGGER.debug(\"xid in RootContext[\" + xid + \"] xid in RpcContext[\" + rpcXid + \"]\");        }        boolean bind = false;        if (xid != null) { // ConsumerÔľöPut XID into the attachment of RPC            RpcContext.getContext().setAttachment(RootContext.KEY_XID, xid);        } else {            if (rpcXid != null) { // ProviderÔľöBind the XID propagated by RPC to current runtime                RootContext.bind(rpcXid);                bind = true;                if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {                    LOGGER.debug(\"bind[\" + rpcXid + \"] to RootContext\");                }            }        }        try {            return invoker.invoke(invocation); // Business method invoke        } finally {            if (bind) { // ProviderÔľöClean up XID after invoke                String unbindXid = RootContext.unbind();                if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {                    LOGGER.debug(\"unbind[\" + unbindXid + \"] from RootContext\");                }                if (!rpcXid.equalsIgnoreCase(unbindXid)) {                    LOGGER.warn(\"xid in change during RPC from \" + rpcXid + \" to \" + unbindXid);                    if (unbindXid != null) { // if there is new transaction begin, can't do clean up                        RootContext.bind(unbindXid);                        LOGGER.warn(\"bind [\" + unbindXid + \"] bac"},"sessionId":"ses_1709336c0ffe4BM0KozFYDlHLu","timestamp":"2026-06-03T21:40:18.240Z","toolInput":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/microservice\"}","toolName":"webfetch","toolOutput":"  Microservice Framework Guide | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/microservice)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/user/microservice)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/user/microservice)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/user/microservice)\n-   [šł≠](/zh-cn/docs/user/microservice)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   User Doc\n-   Microservice Framework Guide\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\n# Transaction Context\n\nTransaction context of Seata is managed by RootContext.\n\nWhen application begins a global transaction, RootContext will bind the XID of the transaction automatically, at the end of transaction(commit or rollback), RootContext will unbind the XID automatically.\n\n```\n// Bind XIDRootContext.bind(xid);// Unbind XIDString xid = RootContext.unbind();\n```\n\nApplication retrieve the global transaction XID through the API of RootContext.\n\n```\n// Retrieve XIDString xid = RootContext.getXID();\n```\n\nWhether application is running a global transaction, just check if an XID bound to RootContext.\n\n```\n    public static boolean inGlobalTransaction() {        return CONTEXT_HOLDER.get(KEY_XID) != null;    }\n```\n\n# Transaction propagation\n\nThe mechanism of the global transaction of Seata is the propagation of transaction context, primarily, it's the propagation way of XID in runtime.\n\n*1\\. The propagation of transaction in the service*\n\nBy default, RootContext is based on ThreadLocal, which is the XID is bound in the context of thread.\n\n```\npublic class ThreadLocalContextCore implements ContextCore {    private ThreadLocal<Map<String, String>> threadLocal = new ThreadLocal<Map<String, String>>() {        @Override        protected Map<String, String> initialValue() {            return new HashMap<String, String>();        }    };    @Override    public String put(String key, String value) {        return threadLocal.get().put(key, value);    }    @Override    public String get(String key) {        return threadLocal.get().get(key);    }    @Override    public String remove(String key) {        return threadLocal.get().remove(key);    }}\n```\n\nSo the inner XID of service is tracing by the same thread naturally, do nothing to propagate the transaction by default.\n\nIf it hopes to hung up the transaction context, implement it by the API of RootContext:\n\n```\n// Hung up(pause)String xid = RootContext.unbind();// TODO: Logic running out of the global transaction scope// recover the global transactionRootContext.bind(xid);\n```\n\n*2\\. Transactional propagation across service calls*\n\nIt's easy to know by the basic idea preceding:\n\n> The transaction propagation across service calls, essentially, propagate the XID via service call to service provider, and bind it to RootContext.\n\nAs long as it can be done, Seata can support any microservice framework in theory.\n\n# Interpretation of supporting Dubbo\n\nLet's interpret the inner support for Dubbo RPC to illustrate how Seata supports a specific microservice framework in follows:\n\nWe use the org.apache.dubbo.rpc.Filter of Dubbo to support propagation of transaction.\n\n```\n/** * The type Transaction propagation filter. */@Activate(group = { Constants.PROVIDER, Constants.CONSUMER }, order = 100)public class TransactionPropagationFilter implements Filter {    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(TransactionPropagationFilter.class);    @Override    public Result invoke(Invoker<?> invoker, Invocation invocation) throws RpcException {        String xid = RootContext.getXID(); // Get XID of current transaction        String rpcXid = RpcContext.getContext().getAttachment(RootContext.KEY_XID); // Acquire the XID from RPC invoke        if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {            LOGGER.debug(\"xid in RootContext[\" + xid + \"] xid in RpcContext[\" + rpcXid + \"]\");        }        boolean bind = false;        if (xid != null) { // ConsumerÔľöPut XID into the attachment of RPC            RpcContext.getContext().setAttachment(RootContext.KEY_XID, xid);        } else {            if (rpcXid != null) { // ProviderÔľöBind the XID propagated by RPC to current runtime                RootContext.bind(rpcXid);                bind = true;                if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {                    LOGGER.debug(\"bind[\" + rpcXid + \"] to RootContext\");                }            }        }        try {            return invoker.invoke(invocation); // Business method invoke        } finally {            if (bind) { // ProviderÔľöClean up XID after invoke                String unbindXid = RootContext.unbind();                if (LOGGER.isDebugEnabled()) {                    LOGGER.debug(\"unbind[\" + unbindXid + \"] from RootContext\");                }                if (!rpcXid.equalsIgnoreCase(unbindXid)) {                    LOGGER.warn(\"xid in change during RPC from \" + rpcXid + \" to \" + unbindXid);                    if (unbindXid != null) { // if there is new transaction begin, can't do clean up                        RootContext.bind(unbindXid);                        LOGGER.warn(\"bind [\" + unbindXid + \"] bac"}}ī#␀wĢˇ